        "origin-eyebrow": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "How It Started",
            "size": "sm",
            "uppercase": true,
            "muted": true
          }
        },
        "origin-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "It Started With a Sourdough Starter",
            "size": "4xl"
          }
        },
        "origin-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>In 2010, Nina Kowalski inherited two things from her grandmother: a 40-year-old sourdough starter and a handwritten recipe book held together with a rubber band. She'd been baking since she could reach the counter, but it was the starter — alive, temperamental, demanding — that turned a hobby into an obsession.</p><p>What started as loaves for friends and neighbors became a farmers market stand, then a tiny storefront, and eventually the bakery you see today. Nina still feeds the starter every morning. Some things you don't mess with.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["origin-eyebrow", "origin-heading", "origin-text"]
    },
    "values": {
      "type": "icon-card-grid",
      "settings": {
        "eyebrow": "What We Believe",
        "title": "The Crumbly Way",
        "columns_desktop": 3,
        "card_layout": "flat",
        "icon_style": "outline",
        "icon_size": "lg",
        "icon_shape": "rounded",
        "color_scheme": "standard-accent"
      },
      "blocks": {
        "value-1": {
          "type": "card",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "clock",
            "title": "Slow Is Better",
            "description": "Long ferments, hand-laminated dough, and patience. We never rush the process because the flavor needs time to develop."
          }
        },
        "value-2": {
          "type": "card",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "leaf",
            "title": "Know Your Ingredients",
            "description": "Organic flour from a family mill upstate. Local butter. Free-range eggs. We know where everything comes from."
          }
        },
        "value-3": {
          "type": "card",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "users",
            "title": "Feed Your Neighbors",
            "description": "We donate unsold bread to the community kitchen every evening. Good food shouldn't go to waste."
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["value-1", "value-2", "value-3"]
